Ask Miss Mannewix
(To submit questions to Miss Mannewix, send them to c647100@showme.
missouri.edu with the words "Ask Miss Mannewix" in the Subject
heading)

Dear Miss Mannewix,

   I have a problem. Every time I post protoproposals to the list,
nobody comments. Then when I go and propose them, they fail! Does
everybody hate me or am I doing something wrong?

                                         Signed,
                                         Frustrated

Dear Frustrated,

   It's not you, it's them. They are too lazy to get up off their
butts and make a few suggestions. Or maybe it is you. You might be
so uncreative that you lull the other Players to sleep with your
droning nonsense. Either way, I sense a large therapy bill for
this dysfunctional family.

                                         Signed,
                                         Miss Mannewix


Dear Miss Mannewix,

   I have this really cool idea for a Rule. You see, we give all
the Players ranks, then hand out Promotion Points based on their
activities. Promotion points are traded in for currencies to spend,
or they can be traded in for more Promotion points. Then we establish
Guilds of Players, and have them compete to devise Rules, which are
then traded among them with the best Rules winning, as adjudged by
the Adjudicator. Disputes are resolved in favor of the Player with the
highest rank, or by the spending of promotion points by the Players'
respective Guilds. Then every two weeks we randomly shift a Player
from one guild to the next, and also choose a Rule to give to the
Guild that lost the Player, which can then trade it in for more
Promotion Points. What do you think?

                                        Signed,
                                        Excited

Dear Excited,

   I think you need less caffeine. Perhaps you can get get together
with Frustrated at a Tibetan retreat somewhere. It'd do both of
you a world of good.

                                        Signed,
                                        Miss Mannewix


